OL,3,C'I'm almost in tears': Man meets staff
OL,4,Cwho saved his life
OL,6,FA man has reunited with the medical
OL,7,Fstaff who saved his life after he
OL,8,Fsuddenly collapsed while out walking.
OL,10,FRay Hughes, 78, was with friends in
OL,11,FRainhill Stoops, near the M62 in
OL,12,FMerseyside, when he went into cardiac
OL,13,Farrest in September 2023.
OL,15,FLuckily, one of the former Merseyside
OL,16,FPolice officer's friends, Greg Wood,
OL,17,Fis a (NWAS) volunteer and recognised
OL,18,Fthe signs.
